According to a report by Intel Market Research, the global Agricultural Spray Oil Market was valued at USD 2.53 billion in 2025 and is projected to reach USD 3.72 billion by 2034, expanding at a CAGR of 5.8% during the forecast period. The market is witnessing steady growth as farmers worldwide increasingly adopt sustainable crop protection practices, integrated pest management (IPM) strategies, and environmentally responsible farming techniques. Agricultural spray oils are widely used both as adjuvants to enhance the performance of pesticides and as standalone pest control agents, providing effective protection against insects, mites, and plant diseases while reducing dependence on conventional synthetic pesticides.
